Description: Wall sherd of East Greek pottery cup; interior black, with an added white-red-white band; exterior, glazed, fired light brown; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 294)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 668, no. 255)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.208)
